Chesebrough-Pond's Inc, recentlyacquired by a unit of Unilever N.V., said it is offering tosell its Bass shoe division, as a result of anongoing evaluation of the long-term direction of itsbusinesses.    The diversified maker of health and beauty aids, said itacquired Falmouth, Maine-based G.H. Bass and Co in 1978, whenthe company reported annual sales of 59 mln dlrs. Bass is knownfor its high-quality casual shoes.    Chesebrough said Bass's 1986 sales exceeded 170 mln dlrs. Reuter&#3;